					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Oh, I am absolutely delighted to read this study. At the back of my mind, I knew barefoot must be good but had a niggling feeling that I might be putting my child at risk. My son is 16 months and has never worn a shoe, so much so that if I try to put shoes on him, he starts howling. We put socks on his feet when we are out; he has recently started to walk but he has never fallen down and from reading this article, it seems like him being barefoot is part of the reason for this. 
</p><p>But I suppose, once he starts to walk outdoors, we may have to protect him from glass etc. and put shoes on him while we are on the streets or park. Don't know how I am going to try and convince him for putting shoes on. Any suggestions anyone?</p>
						
					</div>
