					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I grew up in the country, next to a lake near a beach, and spent as much time as possible barefoot. At 16 I Iearned to drive during the summer, barefoot. I still slip off my shoes on a regular basis for my commute home, as I love driving without shoes. I feel more balanced and connected without shoes, and one of my workout programmes encourages working out barefoot (NIA). I always feel better afterward.  I'll never understand the lure of high heels - they look like amazing sculptures but have no place on the human foot. For shoes, my Ariat riding boots beat everything else by a mile, as they're designed with feel and balance in mind.</p>
						
