					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>On the contrary, when I was a kid I was rarely *allowed* to go barefoot as my mum had read some horror-news-story about a boy who stood on a needle or summat, and consequently had a fear of me stepping on something narsty.  However, my parents always took a lot of care having my shoes properly fitted and making sure they were roomy and flexible, to the extent of sending me to school with a note saying that I wasn't to wear the standard-issue plimsolls, which was highly embarrassing for a 5-year-old!  
</p><p>Seemed to work out for the best though as my feet are in tip-top health now!  albeit a bit wide for most high-street shoes.</p>
						
