							<p>I decided some time ago that my future children will definitely be shoeless animals! TVwriter - hopefully Vibram will start making Fivefingers in kids sizes.
</p><p>I own 2 pairs of Vibrams and 2 of Vivo Barefoots (thankfully due to a great deal in the Brighton Terra Plana outlet for the latter). The Vivos are fine, certainly more comfortable than regular shoes but they don't go all the way. Still have a toe spring for instance. Vibrams for safety but nothing at all is definitely my preference.
</p><p><a shape="rect" href="http://www.hunter-gatherer.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.hunter-gatherer.com</a> is another resource worth checking out.</p>
						
