                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I only started wearing shoes when I turned 2, my mum was convinced that it was better for my feet to grow without constriction. I did grow up in South Africa where it is hot most of the time so that helped. As a child I rarely wore shoes except when I went to school and being barefoot at school was actually totally normal at the Afrikaans schools in my neighbourhood (no, money wasn't the issue). I love walking outside barefoot and always walk in our garden barefoot. My English  partner thinks it's odd, he always wears flip flops in our garden and as a result his feet are too sensitive I think. I waded unhindered into the pebbly sea on our recent trip to Greece while he found the whole experience unbearably painful!</p>
						
