			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-7080335">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/23/Titaflan/3f9e9a14-9d33-4138-9c34-aefbac3d822a/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/Titaflan" title="User profile page">Titaflan</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">9 August 2010 7:02PM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>My little sister howled when my mum tried to put her fat little feet into her startrites eons ago. she was a hardcore barefoot baby. we ran around barefoot all throughout our 1970s childhood, apart from in the city of course, and i remember getting tar on my toes in the summer of 1976 when the roads melted. but it was bliss.
</p><p>my partner has the incredible luck of having trod grapes as a small boy. he said squeezing the grapes between the toes and the ball of the foot was fantastic. what  an amazing memory. my partner's sister who is a chiropodist, says to take off shoes and socks as soon as you're home, and walk around barefoot.</p>
						
					</div>
