					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I had relatives from New Zealand, Auckland, over last month and a one of them, a child of six,  walked around without shoes as often as she could get away with it.  At first I was aghast, thinking about all the germs etc, but I was soon told she did this often in Auckland as it was common to see people walking with out shoes in the streets and supermarkets etc. 
</p><p> I suppose it's what you are used but more importantly having an open mind. Hey men still  wear shoes and socks, or gloves on feet, in the sweltering heat here so we have some time to go!</p>
						
