							<p>I've been <a shape="rect" href="http://barefootrunningadvice.com" rel="nofollow">running barefoot</a> for almost a year now and I have to say that this is the only way i can really run. I used to have terrible pains and aches in my legs and knees when i ran with shoes, but now there is nothing. I'm training for a half marathon this year and i'm up to 8 miles or running without shoes.
<br />by the way MBT are not barefoot shoes, they are the opposite. they offer too much support for your feet to "go natural"</p>
						
